I wish some weapons weren't so ultra rare. There are three or four weapons which you pretty much never see in an actual game with another player. There are a few other minor bugs and problems. When loading an online game it often loads the game you just played instead of the new one you're trying to load up. You need to tap the new game many times and see it load on the left before it'll correctly load the game you want. Also, perhaps because this is an old game, there aren't many people who play regularly these days so you may need to engage in ten or 20 different games at once to take maybe one turn per day. Also the Ninja rope is super buggy and frustrating on a touch screen.

content: üòéCoolüòéüòé
I am a Worms fan, since the very first MS-DOS version.

Similar to other reviews, it's an awesome oldschool game available for a new generation.   The touch controls are a little buggy, so I recommend using the virtual d-pad option. I've played on both my Shield tablet and LG G4, and while the tablet is preferable, the G4 works flawlessly with no lag or issues. As far as a game goes, it isn't horrendous on battery life, which is surprising.  My biggest issue (and main reason for purchasing) is that multiplayer really isn't very well optimized. You can log in via Facebook, Google, or Team17 account, but I can't find any way to link all three. Also, I logged in with my Google account, but my friend logged in with a Team17 account. It was really difficult to find him (my account couldn't search players for a long time), and there is no way to view/verify listings after searching, so if your friend has a common name, good luck figuring out that you have the right person (easily.)  We also had our first match crash and lose data, so had to start over. Since then the following two have been without any problems.

content: Its awesome but please add custom games to local mode.

I played Worms since old DOS versions and must admit this game is awesome. Android version has no serious issues and is very well playable except one problem which disqualifies it for casual gamers - it won't work after a longer break in playing it when at the same time there is no internet connection available. Think travelling abroad without data roaming or flying or staying in a hospital with very bad reception, you want to play a nice game to keep yourself occupied, pick Worms and you see "Problem bla bla bla licensing bla bla". This happened to me MANY TIMES this year only because I did not think about running Worms before traveling just to "enable" licensing. How ridiculous is that?  I've seen licensing FAQ but in this case there is even no need to reinstall the game or fiddle with sync - just running Worms when Internet is available again fixes the problem. Now, Team 17, make licensing less intrusive and I will give 5 stars as the game itself is marvellous. Because I could not play Worms for ALL reasons mentioned above THIS YEAR and I only want to play when I got time for it, I give you 1 star as Worms rarely works when I got that time. FYI I disable background apps

content: This is not a bug report disguised as a negative review. I think the game, functioning as intended, deserves 2 stars. I really enjoyed the part of the game when I was actually playing. It looks and sounds great. My problem with the game is that there's just too much fluff. Consider a typical turn:   1. Overlay with picture of worm and name. (5 seconds, skippable if you control the worm). 2. Walk around, select weapon, aim, shoot. I.e., actual gameplay if you control the worm. 3. Shoot animation (depends, usually a second or two). 4. Slight delay, then damage applied (3-5 seconds). 5. If a worm died, they blow themselves up (3 seconds per worm). 6. Repeat step 4 until no worm dies. 7. Sometimes a crate drops (5 seconds). 7. Turn ends, return to step 1.  Count that up, and you'll see that you're not actually playing very much. I looked for some way to adjust the game speed, shorten animations, etc. but I found nothing. If it's there, it's well-hidden. I felt like I was mostly just watching silly, repetitive animations. If you're the kind of person that like to skip cutscenes (especially ones you've seen), you will find this infuriating, as I did. Too bad.

The most difficult achievement is the "Win 5 ranked matches" award, because no one will finish a match. Seriously, out of 20+ games, only about a quarter of those got finished.  Also, there is a cheat that let's you retake your turn without a joker card... I won't share it, but its not hard to figure out.
Very fun to play , hours of enjoyment for all !!!

content: The game itself is pretty fun.  I enjoy turn based games with friends and this game has definitely been added to the list, however the GUI could use a good amount of TLC. Multiplayer has issues - when playing multiple games it is difficult to switch between the games and way too often it is actually impossible and you have to exit out of the game and go back in to be able to switch. Zooming and panning do not work very well and entirely nonexistent/functional in multiplayer games when you're watching the other person.  You also can't pause or fast forward when watching another person's turn. It is silly that you can't customize the shot clock more - should be able to do way more than 90 seconds if you wanted especially in a custom/non-ranked game. I also get weird cloud sync messages and not sure if I should overwrite or not. And would be nice to have more depth to the solo campaign.  I blew through the available levels and I still suck at this game, hah.  Fix the issues above and will re-rate to at least 4/5 stars.

content: Mixed review on this one. Very close to a huge hit for the Worms crew with  a few nagging issues.  I am finding this game to have a surprisingly low framerate with delayed audio on an Xperia Z2. There is no excuse for this app to have such poor performance on this type of hardware. Admittedly it could be something on my end, but I have yet to figure out what it is.  The touch controls are not so good, feeling sluggish. The gameplay itself is  quite slow. It might just be me, but I remember Worms playing a bit faster. Worm movement is slower than I expected (judging by how hard it is to squeeze your actions into your 60 second turn time). I'm a huge Worms fan, so I might give the tried and true Worms 2 Armageddon a try instead.  That said, I am confident that if there are bug fixes in the pipe, Team17 could turn this right around. The graphics are slick, the sound itself (when not delayed) is designed well, great effects for a mobile game, and interesting game design. The inclusion of "cards" actually spices things up a bit.
replyContent:
Good afternoon Stefan,
We're happy to hear that you find certain aspects of our game 'slick' and 'designed well'.
As for the suggestions above that we have taken note and will forward them onto our developers.
Kind Regards,
Team17 Support
